Multi-talented gospel song writer, Tosin Alao popularly called Sir T, has released a song titled Adaba mimo. The song director’s dexterity cuts across various genres. Sir T is an Afrocentric musician whose style include African fusion mixed with highlife. He also specialises in Afro Balad “Woro” and a bit of reggae and jazz. The Oyo-born grew up in Ibadan where he watched his father, a cleric, play the piano. This childhood experience launched him into the world of music and to the prestigious Obafemi Awolowo University where he studied music.   Keep your hateful comments – Davido’s baby mama     Singer Shina Rambo, wife welcome child     Actress Dorcas Fapson, stylist bicker over alleged debt   Sir T plays guitar, bass, piano and percussions. He is also a music missionary that has established choirs in Africa, Europe and America. Sir T started music professionally in 1986 and is the associate music Pastor & Director of Trinity House. Adaba Mimo is a song full of glory and adoration to God, seeking strength and power from the Almighty to scale through the world of trials and tribulations. It’s a song for everybody and out on all major platforms and exclusively on AllBaze.